column17: "title": "Freeriding The Steep Mountains Of Chamonix | Frozen Mind FULL SNOWBOARD/FREESKI FILM"
column18: "description": "In Frozen Mind
column19: the pro snowboarder Victor de Le Rue is testing the limits of what is possible and challenges himself against unforgiving
column21: France. \n\nChamonix is one of the most prestigious places for mountaineers in the world. Now these dramatic mountains lure more and more skiers and snowboarders to ride the steep
column22: unforgiving faces and it is in Chamonix that we will discover the adventures and evolution of Victor de Le Rue.\n\nIt is being together with his old friend Pierre Hourticq
column23: mountain guide that Victor will try to write a new story in the iconic mountains of the Mont Blanc Massif
column24:
riding extreme slopes of more than 45° that also have extreme consequences.
Frozen Mind is not just a film based on snowboard/ski performance. It is above all a story of friendship and a journey of discovery as the two men take unique paths in order to conquer the same objectives.

Frozen Mind by Ivresse Films
Directed by : Antoine Frioux & Maxime Moulin
Produced by : Antoine Frioux  & Victor de Le Rue
